The '''Armed Forces Financial Network''' (AFFN) is an [[interbank network]] with a mission to increase the versatility of participating financial institutions to better serve the U.S. military. It provides electronic financial transactions services to the military banking and defence credit union sector.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=40329879|title=Company Overview of Armed Forces Financial Network, LLC |accessdate=19 January 2018 |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180119124820/https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=40329879|archivedate=19 January 2018|df=}}</ref> It connects approximately 346 [[bank]]s and [[credit union]]s with over 500,000 [[Automatic teller machine|ATM]]s and 2.3 million [[Point of sale|point-of-sale]] locations that are often in or near military bases both in the United States and overseas.<ref>{{cite web|title=Armed Forces Financial Network and Air Force FCU Donate  “Thank You” Gift Cards to the Lackland Fish - Defense Credit Union Council|url=http://www.dcuc.org/news/278225/DCUC-Member-Credit-Union-Press-Releases-Armed-Forces-Financial-Network.htm|website=www.dcuc.org|accessdate=19 January 2018|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180119120235/http://www.dcuc.org/news/278225/DCUC-Member-Credit-Union-Press-Releases-Armed-Forces-Financial-Network.htm|archivedate=19 January 2018|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Credit Union Joins Armed Forces Financial Network - CUInsight|url=https://www.cuinsight.com/press-release/credit-union-joins-armed-forces-financial-network|website=CUInsight|accessdate=19 January 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180119060628/https://www.cuinsight.com/press-release/credit-union-joins-armed-forces-financial-network|archivedate=19 January 2018|df=}}</ref> John M. Broda is the President and Chief Executive Officer of the Network.<ref>{{cite web|title=Armed Forces Financial Network Announces New President/CEO - Association of Military Banks of America|url=http://www.ambahq.org/news-issues/news/armed-forces-financial-network-announces-new-president-ceo/|website=Association of Military Banks of America|accessdate=19 January 2018|date=19 February 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180119175431/http://www.ambahq.org/news-issues/news/armed-forces-financial-network-announces-new-president-ceo/|archivedate=19 January 2018|df=}}</ref>

==History==
The Armed Forces Financial Network was founded in 1985 at the request of the [[United States Army]] to support the "Surepay" [[direct deposit]] initiative.<ref>{{cite web|title=About Us|url=http://www.affn.org/about-us|website=www.affn.org|accessdate=19 January 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180119060705/http://www.affn.org/about-us|archivedate=19 January 2018|df=}}</ref>  The AFFN's role in the Surepay initiative was to be one way U.S. military personnel could gain access to their money.

In 2017 the Armed Forces Financial Network launched a chip and pin travel card.<ref>{{cite web|title=Armed Forces Financial Network Launches Travel Card - Association of Military Banks of America|url=http://www.ambahq.org/members-section/armed-forces-financial-network-launches-travel-card/|website=Association of Military Banks of America|accessdate=19 January 2018|date=6 August 2013|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180119175425/http://www.ambahq.org/members-section/armed-forces-financial-network-launches-travel-card/|archivedate=19 January 2018|df=}}</ref>

